n errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSecurity Group Management records events such as creating, deleting, or changing security groups, including changes in group members.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004, SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089, SRG-OS-000240-GPOS-00090, SRG-OS-000241-GPOS-00091, SRG-OS-000303-GPOS-00120, SRG-OS-000476-GPOS-00221","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000018","CCI-000172","CCI-001403","CCI-001404","CCI-001405","CCI-002130"],"reference_identifier":"5665","uuid":"bd62edc2-72f6-4b0d-b259-19b0c7e9a550","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DA139B5C39B42B93552CA685C9173D415F0C5BCA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit Account Management - Security Group Management successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254304","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254304","title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254304","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","rule_id_src":"SV-254304r958368_rule","rule_id":"SV-254304","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000110","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit Account Management - User Account Management successes.","fix_text":"Con