der other requirements.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"3890","uuid":"9cc3f5bc-8924-455b-be37-47c3c8f5340e","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 190248D3B8745560D44220D12A015617D48F299A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must restrict anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254470","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254470","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254470","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254470r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254470","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000260","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 services using Local System that use Negotiate when reverting to NTLM authentication must use the computer identity instead of authenticating anonymously.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Network security: Allow Local System to use computer identity for NTLM to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\\n\nValue Name: UseMachineId\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Services using Local System that use Negotiate when reverting to NTLM authentication may gain unauthorized access if allowed to authenticate anonymously versus using the computer identity.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8089","uuid":"ab3452c3-f820-4bda-a908-0db9a043f0f5","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2223C0BF5F429BBE4D1247334EEE25AC27DA1746\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 services using Local System that use Negotiate when reverting to NTLM authentication must use the computer identity instead of authenticating anonymously.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254471","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254471","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254471","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254471r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254471","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000270","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent NTLM from falling back to a Null session.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Network security: Allow LocalSystem NULL session fallback to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: allownullsessionfallback\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"NTLM sessions that are allowed to fall back to Null (unauthenticated) sessions may gain unauthorized access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9223","uuid":"73b40881-f1b8-4d9c-a907-33cf2b50136c","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 603D640153BB7CFEE9DD86BE31ABCEA79CF15902\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must prevent NTLM from falling back to a Null session.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254472","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254472","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254472","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254472r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254472","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000280","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent PKU2U authentication using online identities.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Network security: Allow PKU2U authentication requests to this computer to use online identities to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\pku2u\\\n\nValue Name: AllowOnlineID\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"PKU2U is a peer-to-peer authentication protocol. This setting prevents online identities from authenticating to domain-joined systems. Authentication will be centrally managed with Windows user accounts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5529","uuid":"ce8f5f97-bcf9-4c6d-8a13-5cc0ff97308f","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 749A9653FEFAF05720EFD08AE4F61986687628EA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must prevent PKU2U authentication using online identities.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254473","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254473","title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254473","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","rule_id_src":"SV-254473r971535_rule","rule_id":"SV-254473","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000290","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Kerberos encryption types must be configured to prevent the use of DES and RC4 encryption suites.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Network security: Configure encryption types allowed for Kerberos to \"Enabled\" with only the following selected:\n\nAES128_HMAC_SHA1\nAES256_HMAC_SHA1\nFuture encryption types\n\nNote: Organizations with domain controllers running earlier versions of Windows where RC4 encryption is enabled, selecting \"The other domain supports Kerberos AES Encryption\" on domain trusts, may be required to allow client communication across the trust relationship.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Kerberos\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SupportedEncryptionTypes\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x7ffffff8 (2147483640)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Certain encryption types are no longer considered secure. The DES and RC4 encryption suites must not be used for Kerberos encryption.\n\nNote: Organizations with domain controllers running earlier versions of Windows where RC4 encryption is enabled, selecting \"The other domain supports Kerberos AES Encryption\" on domain trusts, may be required to allow client communication across the trust relationship.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000803"],"reference_identifier":"7553","uuid":"c6568c80-c356-4ff7-9e32-c2519d4179fa","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1419649495CB855CBCC0CC8C04C405D45FB1C5A4\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 Kerberos encryption types must be configured to prevent the use of DES and RC4 encryption suites.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254474","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254474","title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254474","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","rule_id_src":"SV-254474r1051107_rule","rule_id":"SV-254474","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000300","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to prevent the storage of the LAN Manager hash of passwords.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Network security: Do not store LAN Manager hash value on next password change to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: NoLMHash\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The LAN Manager hash uses a weak encryption algorithm and there are several tools available that use this hash to retrieve account passwords. This setting controls whether a LAN Manager hash of the password is stored in the SAM the next time the password is changed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-004062","CCI-000196"],"reference_identifier":"5369","uuid":"1123058f-6034-47d9-9ac2-8c57f2b65d70","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9415549BFB9D63FBC2B2E1FA7B4593B969BF24D9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to prevent the storage of the LAN Manager hash of passwords.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254475","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254475","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254475","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254475r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254475","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000310","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 LAN Manager authentication level must be configured to send NTLMv2 response only and to refuse LM and NTLM.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Network security: LAN Manager authentication level to \"Send NTLMv2 response only. Refuse LM & NTLM\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LmCompatibilityLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000005 (5)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Kerberos v5 authentication protocol is the default for authentication of users who are logging on to domain accounts. NTLM, which is less secure, is retained in later Windows versions for compatibility with clients and servers that are running earlier versions of Windows or applications that still use it. It is also used to authenticate logons to standalone or nondomain-joined computers that are running later versions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5840","uuid":"8e06e334-a464-4746-bf4c-a3ae0bc1bdee","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F1430098ED6C877CFF2E431BF8D202D4BB6D562E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 LAN Manager authentication level must be configured to send NTLMv2 response only and to refuse LM and NTLM.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254476","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254476","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254476","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254476r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254476","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000320","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to at least negotiate signing for LDAP client signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Network security: LDAP client signing requirements to \"Negotiate signing\" at a minimum.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LDAP\\\n\nValue Name: LDAPClientIntegrity\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the signing requirements for LDAP clients. This must be set to \"Negotiate signing\" or \"Require signing\", depending on the environment and type of LDAP server in use.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5666","uuid":"b9e2c474-a42b-44bd-b524-f5919893a457","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1CDAB2ECFE88B12C0D0F9A43B2E513D45EC20090\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to at least negotiate signing for LDAP client signing.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254477","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254477","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254477","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254477r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254477","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000330","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 session security for NTLM SSP-based clients must be configured to require NTLMv2 session security and 128-bit encryption.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) clients to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinClientSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with Remote Procedure Call (RPC) sessions. All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3995","uuid":"e3433900-faab-4559-87ec-e998b5c1de53","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DDA404749A987C4E96F8A5210FE267A9613C13ED\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 session security for NTLM SSP-based clients must be configured to require NTLMv2 session security and 128-bit encryption.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254478","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254478","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254478","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254478r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254478","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000340","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 session security for NTLM SSP-based servers must be configured to require NTLMv2 session security and 128-bit encryption.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) servers to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinServerSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with Remote Procedure Call (RPC) sessions. All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1179","uuid":"d516ccdf-8ee2-4ef2-a06b-9c6f7221778d","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2BC376E266987F18182D616F648F5F1A5BB8BB83\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 session security for NTLM SSP-based servers must be configured to require NTLMv2 session security and 128-bit encryption.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254479","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254479","title":"SRG-OS-000067-GPOS-00035","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254479","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000067-GPOS-00035","rule_id_src":"SV-254479r958450_rule","rule_id":"SV-254479","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000350","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 users must be required to enter a password to access private keys stored on the computer.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> System cryptography: Force strong key protection for user keys stored on the computer to \"User must enter a password each time they use a key\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\\n\nValue Name:  ForceKeyProtection\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If the private key is discovered, an attacker can use the key to authenticate as an authorized user and gain access to the network infrastructure.\n\nThe cornerstone of the PKI is the private key used to encrypt or digitally sign information.\n\nIf the private key is stolen, this will lead to the compromise of the authentication and nonrepudiation gained through PKI because the attacker can use the private key to digitally sign documents and pretend to be the authorized user.\n\nBoth the holders of a digital certificate and the issuing authority must protect the computers, storage devices, or whatever they use to keep the private keys.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000186"],"reference_identifier":"1096","uuid":"d9a5b83d-da33-41f7-a706-4e39ec648b53","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7FA7653DF559D2A8953B5F17456DA4BA97306481\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 users must be required to enter a password to access private keys stored on the computer.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254480","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254480","title":"SRG-OS-000478-GPOS-00223","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254480","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000478-GPOS-00223","rule_id_src":"SV-254480r1137699_rule","rule_id":"SV-254480","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000360","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to use FIPS-compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> System cryptography: Use FIPS compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is NA if the host is running SharePoint.                                                                               If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\FIPSAlgorithmPolicy\\\n\nValue Name: Enabled\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n \nClients with this setting enabled will not be able to communicate via digitally encrypted or signed protocols with servers that do not support these algorithms. Both the browser and web server must be configured to use TLS; otherwise the browser will not be able to connect to a secure site.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting ensures the system uses algorithms that are FIPS-compliant for encryption, hashing, and signing. FIPS-compliant algorithms meet specific standards established by the U.S. Government and must be the algorithms used for all OS encryption functions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"5867","uuid":"8d97498d-ad9e-453b-99b6-6d06ac28d4ea","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2A1DB177F37EB43B7203CEF09EB28E8D323152B7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to use FIPS-compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254481","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254481","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254481","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254481r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254481","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000370","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 default permissions of global system objects must be strengthened.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> System objects: Strengthen default permissions of internal system objects (e.g., Symbolic Links) to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\\n\nValue Name: ProtectionMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows systems maintain a global list of shared system resources such as DOS device names, mutexes, and semaphores. Each type of object is created with a default Discretionary Access Control List (DACL) that specifies who can access the objects with what permissions. When this policy is enabled, the default DACL is stronger, allowing nonadministrative users to read shared objects but not to modify shared objects they did not create.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9274","uuid":"84f47494-1d14-4f8b-bd52-7855fe17f1ed","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8BE99CB2DAD9DFBB390A9437249595EF20C80357\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 default permissions of global system objects must be strengthened.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254482","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254482","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254482","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-254482r1051108_rule","rule_id":"SV-254482","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000380","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) approval mode for the built-in Administrator must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> User Account Control: Admin Approval Mode for the Built-in Administrator account to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: FilterAdministratorToken\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures the built-in Administrator account so that it runs in Admin Approval Mode.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"4140","uuid":"47a03b91-5acc-48bd-9d2c-ac1916514084","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0D80E86DDEFA5E6C8531231AD1AA23F07751486C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) approval mode for the built-in Administrator must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254483","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254483","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254483","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-254483r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-254483","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000390","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 UIAccess applications must not be allowed to prompt for elevation without using the secure desktop.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> User Account Control: Allow UIAccess applications to prompt for elevation without using the secure desktop to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableUIADesktopToggle\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting prevents User Interface Accessibility programs from disabling the secure desktop for elevation prompts.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"5957","uuid":"6962daa9-0ff1-4d1e-b381-52bcdc817291","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 41D09A0A95A9E28B204F06BD026B5932773E8BE9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 UIAccess applications must not be allowed to prompt for elevation without using the secure desktop.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254484","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254484","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254484","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-254484r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-254484","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000400","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must, at a minimum, prompt administrators for consent on the secure desktop.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for administrators in Admin Approval Mode to \"Prompt for consent on the secure desktop\".\n\nThe more secure option for this setting, \"Prompt for credentials on the secure desktop\", would also be acceptable.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ConsentPromptBehaviorAdmin\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2) (Prompt for consent on the secure desktop)\n0x00000001 (1) (Prompt for credentials on the secure desktop)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures the elevation requirements for logged-on administrators to complete a task that requires raised privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"5261","uuid":"27636d51-53d0-4436-9701-85dd69cd6392","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 727DB2E0B19E5FFFF67A3CF446E2F45EF45D3679\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must, at a minimum, prompt administrators for consent on the secure desktop.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254485","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254485","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254485","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-254485r1051109_rule","rule_id":"SV-254485","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000410","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must automatically deny standard user requests for elevation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for standard users to \"Automatically deny elevation requests\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ConsentPromptBehaviorUser\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting controls the behavior of elevation when requested by a standard user account.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"4056","uuid":"fcb9bb5c-ea54-466a-9d0c-ba65f0f2858b","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E5C5BDA76E316E8212A7E0CE43F9EAF07F74C03A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must automatically deny standard user requests for elevation.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254486","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254486","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254486","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-254486r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-254486","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000420","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must be configured to detect application installations and prompt for elevation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> User Account Control: Detect application installations and prompt for elevation to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableInstallerDetection\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting requires Windows to respond to application installation requests by prompting for credentials.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"6947","uuid":"4ec81703-36da-4c63-8aa0-be2f0a2062f1","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1B75DC210FE13D2A80C01386F4EA1E78CDBABEC7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must be configured to detect application installations and prompt for elevation.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254487","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254487","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254487","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-254487r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-254487","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000430","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> User Account Control: Only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSecureUIAPaths\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures Windows to only allow applications installed in a secure location on the file system, such as the Program Files or the Windows\\System32 folders, to run with elevated privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"3836","uuid":"90af6c9b-6c68-49c6-9a3b-7afe2598eeaf","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DB9744A4290F5137AFDA775F38A6FA654793F5CB\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254488","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254488","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254488","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-254488r1051110_rule","rule_id":"SV-254488","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000440","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode, enabling UAC.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> User Account Control: Run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableLUA\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting enables UAC.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"4720","uuid":"a7cfe389-4ec4-4480-960f-dee3e9f4d741","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 947AE653C32B82EBBE908A464349DB70CBE129E1\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode, enabling UAC.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254489","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254489","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254489","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-254489r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-254489","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000450","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> User Account Control: Virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableVirtualization\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures non-UAC-compliant applications to run in virtualized file and registry entries in per-user locations, allowing them to run.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"4087","uuid":"a6f6ac4d-62fd-4c3b-a312-79157fc0a666","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1355579B89F4B5D2AF389162F62A383ED0EA9EF0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254490","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254490","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254490","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254490r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254490","rule_version":"WN22-UC-000010","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must preserve zone information when saving attachments.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Windows to mark file attachments with their zone information.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for User Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Attachment Manager >> Do not preserve zone information in file attachments to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Windows to mark file attachments with their zone information.\n\nIf the registry Value Name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"2\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name: SaveZoneInformation\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attachments from outside sources may contain malicious code. Preserving zone of origin (internet, intranet, local, restricted) information on file attachments allows Windows to determine risk.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1630","uuid":"eab66f59-5316-4eb7-8cab-fef39876b8ba","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 92EC74425A6EC6FFB6C478563C0B5A8E9869A8D2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must preserve zone information when saving attachments.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254491","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254491","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254491","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254491r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254491","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000010","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeTrustedCredManAccessPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right may be able to retrieve the credentials of other accounts from Credential Manager.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"4143","uuid":"152c0976-1cd9-4691-a692-a6e371fcad52","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 80C3FF9A9DF174B0966049E6828549B7E9719DD7\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254492","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254492","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254492","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254492r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254492","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000020","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Act as part of the operating system user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Act as part of the operating system to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups (to include administrators), are granted the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeTcbPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).\n\nPasswords for accounts with this user right must be protected as highly privileged accounts.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right can assume the identity of any user and gain access to resources that the user is authorized to access. Any accounts with this right can take complete control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8148","uuid":"b941a546-8488-4fac-9963-e86306fe8115","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E08920ED22B2B9BEB3B7812E2AE9B40DE3F6A4E8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Act as part of the operating system user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254493","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254493","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254493","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-254493r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-254493","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000030","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Allow log on locally user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Allow log on locally to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Allow log on locally\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeInteractiveLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Allow log on locally\" user right can log on interactively to a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"4704","uuid":"1b8e7d34-332a-4e1c-a9f3-0ccd79058ed2","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 77C3104F090B54FA77628EFD079822B6CC93F201\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Allow log on locally user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254494","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254494","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254494","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254494r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254494","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000040","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 back up files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Back up files and directories to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Back up files and directories\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeBackupPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Back up files and directories\" user right can circumvent file and directory permissions and could allow access to sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"7755","uuid":"d00b21ab-2283-42ba-b1eb-34b95d707371","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 47BDF03FB04867D26AA65AE133D5AF7B89AA37D2\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 back up files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254495","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254495","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254495","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254495r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254495","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000050","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 create a pagefile user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Create a pagefile to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Create a pagefile\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeCreatePagefilePrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create a pagefile\" user right can change the size of a pagefile, which could affect system performance.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"7265","uuid":"8b2cd221-625c-45fc-b288-2b99349ebe3e","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CA78A976E09FEE6FE9081EDFA96F1C7406D83749\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 create a pagefile user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254496","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254496","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254496","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254496r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254496","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000060","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 create a token object user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Create a token object to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Create a token object\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeCreateTokenPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).\n\nPasswords for application accounts with this user right must be protected as highly privileged accounts.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Create a token object\" user right allows a process to create an access token. This could be used to provide elevated rights and compromise a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5194","uuid":"af388a2c-fa49-467f-ac93-f67cc4f1b6b8","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6AD709F594CD48FFF8D3636ED6BD88023053BECA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 create a token object user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254497","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254497","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254497","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254497r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254497","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000070","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 create global objects user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Create global objects to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators\n- Service\n- Local Service\n- Network Service","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Create global objects\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n- Service\n- Local Service\n- Network Service\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeCreateGlobalPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\nS-1-5-6 (Service)\nS-1-5-19 (Local Service)\nS-1-5-20 (Network Service)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create global objects\" user right can create objects that are available to all sessions, which could affect processes in other users' sessions.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3599","uuid":"7ca0258d-5d0b-4c61-9cd5-f6226eff53d6","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 47F42EAD095027C0E2C97D9CF4623952040112C8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 create global objects user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254498","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254498","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254498","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254498r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254498","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000080","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 create permanent shared objects user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Create permanent shared objects to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeCreatePermanentPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right could expose sensitive data by creating shared objects.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8340","uuid":"454e6e81-9395-4e7e-8148-21ff3655eaca","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6AE072A18268B2C4ED51EB8FF55966F5A65B6679\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 create permanent shared objects user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254499","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254499","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254499","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254499r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254499","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000090","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 create symbolic links user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Create symbolic links to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators\n\nSystems that have the Hyper-V role will also have \"Virtual Machines\" given this user right. If this needs to be added manually, enter it as \"NT Virtual Machine\\Virtual Machines\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Create symbolic links\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeCreateSymbolicLinkPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nSystems that have the Hyper-V role will also have \"Virtual Machines\" given this user right (this may be displayed as \"NT Virtual Machine\\Virtual Machines\", SID S-1-5-83-0). This is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create symbolic links\" user right can create pointers to other objects, which could expose the system to attack.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9955","uuid":"5f2a9346-fbb1-45bb-afe7-bc45233b9bb5","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2E274A6C3D69DD43051A0D0085EFD1A29C340D3D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 create symbolic links user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254500","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254500","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254500","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254500r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254500","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000100","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 debug programs user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Debug programs to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Debug programs\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeDebugPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).\n\nPasswords for application accounts with this user right must be protected as highly privileged accounts.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Debug programs\" user right can attach a debugger to any process or to the kernel, providing complete access to sensitive and critical operating system components. This right is given to Administrators in the default configuration.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"6400","uuid":"22752133-3949-40ef-989c-1689fe80d65f","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6B27E5BBBFB7D539869DAD40B704BD8947CAE64A\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 debug programs user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254501","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254501","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254501","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254501r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254501","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000110","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 force shutdown from a remote system user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Force shutdown from a remote system to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeRemoteShutdownPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right can remotely shut down a system, which could result in a denial of service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5815","uuid":"dd1c8cb8-b524-499e-afa3-f9fd42670a2f","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C70D33AEE6EB75F07F91ADC7FC33BDF703845831\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 force shutdown from a remote system user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254502","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254502","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254502","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254502r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254502","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000120","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 generate security audits user right must only be assigned to Local Service and Network Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Generate security audits to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Local Service\n- Network Service","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Generate security audits\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Local Service\n- Network Service\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeAuditPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-19 (Local Service)\nS-1-5-20 (Network Service)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Generate security audits\" user right specifies users and processes that can generate Security Log audit records, which must only be the system service accounts defined.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8704","uuid":"d466010e-1dc4-4852-8560-e40d4396e53b","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B7D1330CF0E3745590B19CC87C3F7D1B57B7F13D\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 generate security audits user right must only be assigned to Local Service and Network Service.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254503","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254503","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254503","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254503r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254503","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000130","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 impersonate a client after authentication user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Impersonate a client after authentication to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators\n- Service\n- Local Service\n- Network Service","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n- Service\n- Local Service\n- Network Service\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeImpersonatePrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\nS-1-5-6 (Service)\nS-1-5-19 (Local Service)\nS-1-5-20 (Network Service)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right allows a program to impersonate another user or account to run on their behalf. An attacker could use this to elevate privileges.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3231","uuid":"3ca48a40-29dd-4a61-9e9d-141a693045ad","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 748C925A3B11FC209C9AD466490A7E887E8E057E\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 impersonate a client after authentication user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254504","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254504","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254504","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254504r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254504","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000140","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 increase scheduling priority: user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Increase scheduling priority to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Increase scheduling priority\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeIncreaseBasePriorityPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Increase scheduling priority\" user right can change a scheduling priority, causing performance issues or a denial of service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3868","uuid":"ab1b886f-ddfd-41c3-b93d-634798ac7565","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7AC4381FF1A5D29A048D5FF65736BEF6D35FF271\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 increase scheduling priority: user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254505","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254505","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254505","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254505r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254505","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000150","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 load and unload device drivers user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Load and unload device drivers to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Load and unload device drivers\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeLoadDriverPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Load and unload device drivers\" user right allows a user to load device drivers dynamically on a system. This could be used by an attacker to install malicious code.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2057","uuid":"fb1a75f1-3301-4d5b-9e21-f617fa0fa3a0","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 289783789C439BF1B527D3C22296DA244B06787B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 load and unload device drivers user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254506","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254506","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254506","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254506r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254506","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000160","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 lock pages in memory user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Lock pages in memory to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Lock pages in memory\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeLockMemoryPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Lock pages in memory\" user right allows physical memory to be assigned to processes, which could cause performance issues or a denial of service.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125, SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00193","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235","CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"5327","uuid":"51ddf6e7-a834-4dcf-bc87-ca507b931eb6","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9FF0E91E2FA4BEB3BFC7DD7C1BA978938DAE41C5\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 lock pages in memory user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254507","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254507","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254507","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","rule_id_src":"SV-254507r958434_rule","rule_id":"SV-254507","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000170","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 manage auditing and security log user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Manage auditing and security log to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Manage auditing and security log\" user right, this is a finding.\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeSecurityPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf the organization has an Auditors group, the assignment of this group to the user right would not be a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Manage auditing and security log\" user right can manage the security log and change auditing configurations. This could be used to clear evidence of tampering.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029, SRG-OS-000063-GPOS-00032, SRG-OS-000337-GPOS-00129","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164","CCI-000171","CCI-001914"],"reference_identifier":"7612","uuid":"c3893597-193f-4d92-b6bd-72e6ec805fc8","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 09136F3BEEC92C591559085AEE2A91ED20E04EB3\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 manage auditing and security log user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254508","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254508","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254508","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254508r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254508","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000180","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 modify firmware environment values user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Modify firmware environment values to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Modify firmware environment values\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeSystemEnvironmentPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Modify firmware environment values\" user right can change hardware configuration environment variables. This could result in hardware failures or a denial of service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"7291","uuid":"c880e027-8fe2-4203-b357-3b4e9c6a872b","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BF473DEBA3C969886036608F34D1294C986A5BC6\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 modify firmware environment values user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254509","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254509","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254509","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254509r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254509","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000190","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 perform volume maintenance tasks user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Perform volume maintenance tasks to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Perform volume maintenance tasks\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeManageVolumePrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Perform volume maintenance tasks\" user right can manage volume and disk configurations. This could be used to delete volumes, resulting in data loss or a denial of service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"9481","uuid":"fdd33616-d551-4ba0-8e77-06c30c82c3b9","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AD5218B69514B87031A837F242342A30337B3491\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 perform volume maintenance tasks user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254510","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254510","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254510","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254510r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254510","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000200","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 profile single process user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Profile single process to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Profile single process\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeProfileSingleProcessPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Profile single process\" user right can monitor nonsystem processes performance. An attacker could use this to identify processes to attack.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8406","uuid":"fd459dc1-f4e0-4eed-a5bd-7f6c5038d299","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 42300EF01482AB572EF308C077A1C370EBDDF3E9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 profile single process user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254511","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254511","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254511","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254511r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254511","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000210","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 restore files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Restore files and directories to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Restore files and directories\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeRestorePrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Restore files and directories\" user right can circumvent file and directory permissions and could allow access to sensitive data. It could also be used to overwrite more current data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"7227","uuid":"371eed14-f06b-4de8-9008-1aa8f580025f","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8287FCF5F71D64EA9521F2E52873475BAD67B48A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 restore files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254512","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254512","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254512","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254512r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254512","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000220","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 take ownership of files or other objects user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Take ownership of files or other objects to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeTakeOwnershipPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" user right can take ownership of objects and make changes.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8965","uuid":"084794ef-c6ea-47ca-aa83-9f06aea50cc6","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: BFFF9F69A3B691ED1E9EB280FCBD0DDC88927B23\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 take ownership of files or other objects user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271426","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271426","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271426","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-271426r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-271426","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000405","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured for certificate-based authentication for domain controllers.","fix_text":"Configure the registry value.\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Kdc\n \nValue Name: StrongCertificateBindingEnforcement\n \nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) or 0x00000002 (2)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. This is not applicable for member servers.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Kdc\n \nValue Name: StrongCertificateBindingEnforcement\n \nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) or 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Active Directory domain services elevation of privilege vulnerability could allow a user rights to the system, such as administrative and other high-level capabilities.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"2871","uuid":"5db27b8a-1bb0-4715-9418-62073ac8c062","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 34247E83545B8E8FE36A2C7EA50B188C0AAD31C2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured for certificate-based authentication for domain controllers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-271427","group_tree":[{"id":"V-271427","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-271427","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-271427r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-271427","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000406","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured for name-based strong mappings for certificates.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Template >> System >> KDC >> Allow name-based strong mappings for certificates to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. This is not applicable for member servers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Administrative Template >> System >> KDC >> Allow name-based strong mappings for certificates.\n\nIf \"Allow name-based strong mappings for certificates\" is not \"Enabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Weak mappings give rise to security vulnerabilities and demand hardening measures. Certificate names must be correctly mapped to the intended user account in Active Directory. A lack of strong name-based mappings allows certain weak certificate mappings, such as Issuer/Subject AltSecID and User Principal Names (UPN) mappings, to be treated as strong mappings.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"8378","uuid":"4bd17d64-4165-4d30-936c-9508ae074b1b","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 741A6A395F5550958119C09C38BA23B274260751\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured for name-based strong mappings for certificates.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-278942","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278942","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278942","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278942r1135355_rule","rule_id":"SV-278942","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000581","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit file system failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit File System\" with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit File System auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> Audit File System. \n\nIf \"Audit File System\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"1704","uuid":"3157c6a2-7d04-48f2-964b-87ee9a44d043","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 29D527DE5CFB940491FD9C287A5F9B14BF66287B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit file system failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-278943","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278943","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-278943","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-278943r1135358_rule","rule_id":"SV-278943","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000582","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit file system successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> \"Audit File System\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify that Audit File System auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Object Access >> Audit File System. \n\nIf \"Audit File System\" is not set to \"Success\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"3528","uuid":"a4ee3267-78c7-4974-a5db-71c6201b712b","stig_uuid":"a9a1a010-32d2-40cd-921a-49064ba0c378","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 63CE880D31C2207D73E49DB42A7ACA64CFD2EF74\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit file system successes.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-278944","group_tree":[{"id":"V-278944","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}